<!--
Template for a per-paper markdown file. Created by /import-results, one per deduplicated record
imported from raw/exports/. Subsequent skills APPEND new sub-sections; they never rewrite prior
sub-sections in place.

This file is the source-of-truth for the paper. The xlsx spreadsheet is regenerated from it
(plus all other paper-NNNN.md files) on every commit by the post-commit hook.

Filename convention: `papers/paper-NNNN.md` — NNNN is a 4-digit zero-padded auto-incrementing id
assigned at import time and stable across the entire review (`paper-0014`, `paper-0223`,
`paper-2139`, …, up to `paper-9999`).

Two-pass screening with accretive audit trail (v3 Phase 3 — PLUGIN-SPEC §20.9): each of stages
04/05/06 records the decision history as `### iter-K` sub-sections plus a final `### final`
block. iter-0 is written by the first run of the screening skill (combining the pass-1 regex
record and the pass-2 LLM record); subsequent iter-K blocks are written by `screen --refine`
when the user refines `protocols/classifier-config.json` mid-screening. The
`### final` block is written at lock time and carries the user's verdict plus a pointer back to
the iteration whose classification was kept (`locked_at_iteration: iter-K`).
-->

---
id: paper-NNNN
title: "<full title>"
authors:
  - "<Last, First>"
  - "<Last, First>"
venue: "<conference or journal name>"
venue_type: "<conference | journal | book-chapter>"
year: <YYYY>
doi: "<10.xxxx/yyyy or empty>"
url: "<publisher URL or empty>"
publisher: "<publisher>"
pages: "<start–end or empty>"
keywords:
  - "<kw1>"
  - "<kw2>"
language: "<en | pt | other>"

# Provenance of this record (filled by /03-parse-references-metadata)
source:
  databases: ["<Scopus>", "<IEEE Xplore>"]     # databases where the paper was returned
  exports: ["raw/exports/scopus-2025-09-14.bib"] # export files it came from
  imported_at: "<YYYY-MM-DD>"
  dedup:
    merged_from: []                              # ids of duplicates merged into this one
    merge_reason: ""                             # "same DOI" | "same title+year+first-author" | etc.

# Per-stage status — updated at each stage lock. Drives xlsx regeneration and stage gates.
# `unavailable` (stage 06 only) marks papers whose PDF could not be obtained.
status:
  04-title-screening:      pending   # pending | include | exclude
  05-abstract-screening:   pending   # pending | include | exclude
  06-full-text-screening:  pending   # pending | include | exclude | unavailable
  07-taxonomy-development: pending   # pending | coded | classified
  08-analysis:             pending

# Two-pass screening record per stage. The frontmatter mirrors the *latest* iteration's
# regex+LLM verdict plus the human-edited fields. The full iteration history lives in the body
# as `### iter-K (...)` sub-sections; `last_iteration` here points at the iteration whose values
# the frontmatter currently mirrors. `locked_at_iteration` is set at lock time and points at the
# iteration the user kept; the corresponding `### final` block in the body carries the verdict.
# See `agents/_screening-protocol.md §7`.
screening:
  04-title-screening:
    last_iteration:          0      # integer K — latest iter-K written for this stage
    proposed_decision:       null   # Include | Exclude | null  (mirror of iter-K regex_decision)
    proposed_justification:  null   # verbatim PT-BR string from the winning category | null
    winning_category:        null   # category id | "default" | null
    overrides_applied:       []     # list of override ids hit during pass 1 of iter-K
    my_final_decision:       null   # Include | Exclude | null (user-editable via xlsx col L)
    my_justification:        null   # 1–3 sentences PT-BR | null (user-editable via xlsx col M)
    agrees_with_regex:       null   # true | false | null
    divergence_reason:       null   # 1–2 sentences PT-BR when agrees_with_regex == false | null
    locked_at_iteration:     null   # "iter-K" — the iteration kept at lock time | null
    locked_at:               null   # ISO timestamp of [04] lock | null
  05-abstract-screening:
    last_iteration:          0
    proposed_decision:       null
    proposed_justification:  null
    winning_category:        null
    overrides_applied:       []
    my_final_decision:       null
    my_justification:        null
    agrees_with_regex:       null
    divergence_reason:       null
    locked_at_iteration:     null
    locked_at:               null
  06-full-text-screening:
    last_iteration:          0
    proposed_decision:       null
    proposed_justification:  null
    winning_category:        null
    overrides_applied:       []
    my_final_decision:       null
    my_justification:        null
    agrees_with_regex:       null
    divergence_reason:       null
    locked_at_iteration:     null
    locked_at:               null

# Taxonomy classification — populated during `07-taxonomy-development` after `taxonomy-locked`.
# Keys are axis names declared in CLAUDE.md §8.1; values come from the code book §8.2.
taxonomy: {}
---

# paper-NNNN — `<short title or key phrase>`

The body of this file is organized as an accretive log. Each stage appends its own section in order. Prior sections are never rewritten in place; corrections happen via checkpoint commits that materialize a new `### Reviewed (LLM)` block (the latest one is the source-of-truth; older blocks remain in git history).

## Metadata (from `/03-parse-references-metadata`)

Short prose summary of the record. Full machine-readable fields live in the frontmatter.

**Abstract**

> `<paste abstract verbatim; keep original language>`

**Dedup notes**

`<If this record was merged with duplicates from other databases, note what was merged and why. Otherwise: "no duplicates found".>`

