## 06 — Full-Text Screening

Populated by `/screen --stage full-text`. Requires `raw/pdfs/paper-NNNN.pdf` (or a `papers/paper-NNNN.fulltext.md` produced by `/prepare-pdf`). Pass 1 reads the section-anchored excerpt; pass 2 reads the same. Justifications cite section labels (e.g., "§4.2 confirma o claim do abstract").

- **PDF location:** `raw/pdfs/paper-NNNN.pdf`
- **Fulltext location:** `papers/paper-NNNN.fulltext.md` (when produced by `/prepare-pdf`)

### iter-0 (initial classification)

- **regex_decision:** `<Include | Exclude>`
- **regex_justification:** `"<verbatim PT-BR string>"`
- **winning_category:** `<category_id | default>`
- **overrides_applied:** `[<override_id>, …]`
- **evidence_trail:**
  - `{ category: <category_id>, pattern_id: <pattern_id>, matched_substring: "<substring>", position: [<start>, <end>], section: "<section label or null>" }`
  - `{ … }`
- **llm_decision:** `<Include | Exclude>`
- **llm_justification:** `"<1–3 sentences PT-BR; cite a section label>"`
- **agrees_with_regex:** `<true | false>`
- **divergence_reason:** `<null | "<cite a section label>">`
- **model:** `<model id>`
- **timestamp:** `<ISO timestamp>`

### final

- **my_final_decision:** `<Include | Exclude>` (or `unavailable` when no PDF could be obtained)
- **my_justification:** `"<free text — must cite a section label>"`
- **locked_at_iteration:** `<iter-K>`
- **locked_at:** `<ISO timestamp of [06] lock>`

